<Content>hard to find, hard to leave We spent just one night as a part of our tour of Bali, but we immediately fell in love with this place. The location is certainly off the beaten track, about three hours from the international airport and about fifteen minutes uphill drive from the northern coast of Bali.Once you're there, the hotel with it's beautiful grounds is like paradise, very luxurious but maintaining a relaxed, cosy atmosphere. There are only a handful of rooms which are actually little houses. Ours had the shower and a whirlpool outside, in a lovely little private walled-garden. The room itself was spacious, clean and luxuriously appointed. The main-pool isn't huge, but very nice, with a great view.The highlight of our stay was the dinner. The cuisine was excellent and by far the best we've experienced on Bali.Altogether, the hotel offers excellent value compared to other high-end options on Bali, the drawback obviously being the location. However, there is plenty to see on the way, so you can make the most of the transfer by making sure you have plenty of time and a driver who knows the sights.I think this hotel is a perfect place to relax, read and enjoy great food. 
